description: The ancient name "Timavus" denoted a river that flowed partly underground east of the city of Aquileia, emptying into the Gulf of Trieste. Its visible upper course is known today as the Reka; its visible lower course as the Timavo.
details: BAtlDir associates the ancient Timavus with the modern Timavo, but the label in BAtlas is clearly attached to the course of the modern Isonzo. The course of the modern Timavo does not appear on the BAtlas map 19 at all.
